					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This article has been to hell and back again, bouncing around from infohazards, to pataphysics, to infohazards again, to where we are now. Special thanks to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/reverend-fox" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1893953&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1567450281" alt="Reverend Fox" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1893953)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/reverend-fox" >Reverend Fox</a></span> and <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/crow-cat" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3952131&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1567450281" alt="Crow-Cat" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3952131)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/crow-cat" >Crow-Cat</a></span> for their invaluable feedback and critique during the creation of this article, and to the Park Rangers at the Canaveral National Seashore for literally pointing me in the right direction.</p> <p><strong>Photo Credit:</strong> Me and my camera :^)</p> <p><strong>Photo Details:</strong> A mature gopher tortoise living in the Canaveral National Seashore area.<br /> (F/5, 1/1250 Sec, ISO-200, 4.6 Apt.)</p> <p>I hope you all enjoy the read!<br /> <span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span></p> <hr /> <p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><br /> Also, huge thanks to the SCP Cafe podcast for reviewing this piece in their <strong><a href="https://scp.cafe/2019/01/25/recap-2019-week-3/">Recap: 2019, Week 3</a></strong> episode! You guys are awesome!<br /> <span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span></p> 
				 	]]>
